# 🤖 ML Model Comparison Dashboard

A fully interactive **Streamlit web application** for end-to-end machine learning workflows — from data upload to model comparison, prediction, and result download.

---

## 🚀 Features

### 📂 1. Dataset Upload

* Upload CSV datasets بسهولة
* Automatic detection of:

  * Data types
  * Missing values
  * Column statistics

### 🔍 2. Data Exploration

* Statistical summaries
* Categorical analysis
* Outlier detection (IQR method)
* Class distribution visualization

### 📊 3. Data Visualization

* Correlation heatmaps
* Histograms & distributions
* Pair plots
* Scatter & box plots

### ⚙️ 4. Data Preprocessing

* Missing value handling:

  * Drop / Mean / Median / Mode
* Encoding:

  * Label Encoding
  * One-Hot Encoding
* Feature scaling:

  * StandardScaler
  * MinMaxScaler
* Train-test splitting

### 🤖 5. Supervised Learning

Supports both:

* **Classification**
* **Regression**

#### Models Included:

* Logistic Regression / Linear Regression
* Decision Tree
* Random Forest
* KNN
* SVM
* Naive Bayes (classification only)
* Gradient Boosting

#### Metrics:

* Classification: Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1 Score
* Regression: MAE, MSE, R² Score
* Cross-validation scores

---

### 🔮 6. Unsupervised Learning (Clustering)

* K-Means
* Hierarchical Clustering
* DBSCAN
* Gaussian Mixture Models

#### Evaluation:

* Silhouette Score
* Davies-Bouldin Score
* PCA-based cluster visualization

---

### 🏆 7. Best Model Selection

* Automatically selects the best model
* Displays:

  * Performance metrics
  * Learning curves
  * Model comparison

---

### 🎯 8. Prediction Interface

* Dynamic input form
* Real-time predictions
* Prediction history tracking

---

### 📥 9. Download Results

* Trained model (`.pkl`)
* Processed dataset (`.csv`)
* Prediction results (`.csv`)
* Model comparison report (`.csv`)
* Clustering report (`.csv`)

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

* **Frontend/UI**: Streamlit
* **Data Handling**: Pandas, NumPy
* **Visualization**: Plotly, Matplotlib, Seaborn
* **Machine Learning**: Scikit-learn

---

## 📦 Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/ml-dashboard.git

# Navigate to project folder
cd ml-dashboard

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## ▶️ Run the App

```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
ml-dashboard/
│── app.py
│── requirements.txt
│── README.md
```

---

## 💡 How to Use

1. Upload your dataset
2. Explore and visualize data
3. Preprocess features
4. Train models
5. Compare performance
6. Select best model
7. Make predictions
8. Download results

---

## ⚡ Key Highlights

* End-to-end ML workflow in one app
* Beginner-friendly UI
* Supports both supervised & unsupervised learning
* No coding required for model training
* Interactive visualizations

